lzh_formatted:
  title: 客夜
  author: 鄭夢周
  language: lzh
  text: 客夜人誰問。沉吟欲二更。詩從枕上得。燈在壁閒明。默默思前事。遙遙計去程。俄然睡一覺。童僕報鷄鳴。
korean:
  title: 객야
  author: 정몽주
  language: kor
  text: |-
    나그네 밤에 누가 찾으리
    혼자 읊조리니 이경이 되려 하네
    시는 베개 위로 쫓아 얻고
    등잔불은 벽 사이에 밝네
    묵묵히 지난 일을 생각하고
    곰곰이 갈길을 헤어 보네
    깜빡 졸다가 깨니
    아이놈이 닭이 운다 하더라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0130_010_0360&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Traveler's Night
  author: Jung Mong-ju
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Who comes to visit a traveler in the night?
    Alone I murmur verses as the second watch draws near.
    Poems are plucked from my pillow,
    Lantern light gleams through the wall's narrow gap.
    Silently I ponder what has passed,
    Carefully I measure the road ahead.
    Suddenly sleep takes me in its brief embrace—
    Then a servant's voice: the rooster crows at dawn.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'second watch' (二更) refers to the traditional divided night; this would be approximately 10 PM, suggesting deep contemplation in the small hours.
  - key: ''
    value: The image of poems coming 'from the pillow' suggests dreams and inspiration arising from the solitude of travel and reflection.
